gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 114, Trail Blazers 111
gameRecap.excerpt: Denver defeats Portland, 114-111. For Denver, Aaron Gordon led the way with 22 points, 12 rebounds, five assists, and three blocks while aided by Reggie Jackson (23 points, five assists, two steals) and Christian Braun (17 points, eight rebounds, six assists, three steals) in the victory. Duop Reath finished with 24 points (three 3PM), eight rebounds, and two blocks with Scoot Henderson recording 22 points, six assists, and two steals while Toumani Camara added 16 points, seven rebounds, and six assists for Portland in the losing effort. Denver improves to 50-21, while Portland moves to 19-52 in the loss.
